# Phase 54: Emergency UI Recovery & Symmetry Restoration

The goal is to fix the UI regressions introduced in V5.2.25 and restore the professional, high-fidelity aesthetic of the "Transactions" page.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] UI Enterprise Shell (app.js)

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js)
- **Title Restoration**:
  - Revert header title "Forensic Ledger" back to **"Transactions"**.
  - Update subtitle to **"V5.2 • High-Performance Ledger"** (removing any "Audit-Ready" or overly descriptive forensic terminology if annoying).
- **Grid Formatter Fix**:
  - Remove accidental spaces from HTML strings in all Tabulator column formatters (e.g., change `< span` to `<span>` and `</span >` to `</span>`).
  - This affects columns: Date, Payee / Description, Debit, Credit, Balance, Account, and Source.
- **Symmetry & Polish**:
  - Ensure the Switcher Bar and Action Bar maintain perfect horizontal alignment.
  - Remove any placeholder text that might be perceived as a "joke" (e.g., "WAITING TO GET STARTED").

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Verify that the grid renders real data again (no raw HTML tags visible).
- Verify the header title correctly displays "Transactions".
- Ensure the reconciliation hub in the switcher bar remains functional but looks professional.
- Check horizontal symmetry across the entire island stack.

## Phase 55: Grid Header Refinement

The goal is to sharpen the header visual structure and ensure left-aligned uniformity for all column titles.

### [Component] UI Enterprise Shell (app.js & system.css)

#### [MODIFY] [system.css](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/system.css)
- **Sharpen Dividers**:
  - Increase `.tabulator-col` border-right to `1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8)` for maximum definition.
- **Left Indented Text**:
  - Update `.tabulator-col-content` to explicitly use `justify-content: flex-start !important`.

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js)
- **Uniform Alignment**:
  - Add `headerHozAlign: "left"` to all columns in the Tabulator configuration.

## Phase 56: UI Scaling & Performance Optimization

The goal is to increase visibility by scaling the top 3 cards by 20% and optimizing the switcher logic for high-performance responsiveness.

### [Component] UI Enterprise Shell (app.js & system.css)

#### [MODIFY] [system.css](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/system.css)
- **Island Scale**:
  - Increase max-width from `1166px` to `1400px` (~20% increase).
- **Component Scaling**:
  - Increase Header height, Action Bar height (~53px), and Switcher Bar density.
  - Scale font-sizes by ~20% (e.g., 11px -> 13px, 12.5px -> 15px).

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js)
- **Account Switcher Optimization**:
  - Change default `selectedAccount` from `'ALL'` to the first available account ID.
  - Streamline [switchAccount](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js#262-304) logic to prevent redundant re-renders.
  - Ensure "ALL" is an optional toggle rather than the default entry point.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Verify the header/action/switcher cards appear 20% larger and more readable.
- Confirm the system defaults to an individual account view on load.
- Verify column dividers are sharp and text is left-aligned.
